11
00:05:57,451 --> 00:06:00,155
Are there any questions before we proceed?

12
00:06:00,246 --> 00:06:02,571
I have one question, Dr Frankenstein.

13
00:06:05,376 --> 00:06:07,582
That's Fronkonsteen.

14
00:06:07,670 --> 00:06:09,627
I beg your pardon?

15
00:06:10,048 --> 00:06:13,417
My name. It's pronounced "Fronkonsteen".

16
00:06:13,510 --> 00:06:17,507
But aren't you the grandson
of the famous Dr Victor Frankenstein,...

17
00:06:17,598 --> 00:06:22,592
..who dug up freshly buried corpses
and transformed dead components into...

18
00:06:22,686 --> 00:06:24,346
Yes, yes!

19
00:06:24,438 --> 00:06:25,552
Yes!

20
00:06:25,648 --> 00:06:27,724
We all know what he did!

21
00:06:28,651 --> 00:06:33,396
But I'd rather be remembered
for my own small contributions to science...

22
00:06:34,324 --> 00:06:37,527
..and not because of
my accidental relationship...

23
00:06:38,036 --> 00:06:41,286
..to a famous... cuckoo!

24
00:06:45,252 --> 00:06:47,956
Now, if you don't mind,
can we have your question?

25
00:06:48,046 --> 00:06:51,379
Well, sir, I'm not sure
I understand the distinction...

26
00:06:51,467 --> 00:06:54,551
..between reflexive
and voluntary nerve impulses.

27
00:06:54,637 --> 00:06:58,884
Good. Since our lab work today
is a demonstration of just that distinction,...

28
00:06:58,975 --> 00:07:01,051
..why don't we proceed?

29
00:07:10,779 --> 00:07:14,148
Mr Hilltop here,
with whom I have never worked...

30
00:07:14,241 --> 00:07:17,076
..or given any prior instructions to,...

31
00:07:17,161 --> 00:07:21,158
..has graciously offered his services
for today's demonstration.

32
00:07:21,791 --> 00:07:26,204
Mr Hilltop, would you hop up on your feet
and stand beside this table?

33
00:07:36,014 --> 00:07:38,090
Nice... hopping.

34
00:07:40,227 --> 00:07:42,303
Mr Hilltop,...

35
00:07:42,730 --> 00:07:47,558
..would you raise... your left knee, please?

36
00:07:50,571 --> 00:07:53,904
You have just witnessed
a voluntary nerve impulse.

37
00:07:53,992 --> 00:07:57,076
lt begins as a stimulus
from the cerebral cortex,...

38
00:07:57,162 --> 00:08:00,661
..passes through the brainstem
and to the muscles involved.

39
00:08:00,749 --> 00:08:03,074
Mr Hilltop, you may lower your knee.

40
00:08:03,168 --> 00:08:08,411
Reflex movements are those
which are made independently of the will,...

41
00:08:08,507 --> 00:08:10,748
..but are carried out along pathways...

42
00:08:10,843 --> 00:08:15,339
..which pass between the peripheral nervous
system and the central nervous system.

43
00:08:15,431 --> 00:08:17,756
You filthy, rotten, yellow son of a bitch!

44
00:08:18,976 --> 00:08:21,549
We are not aware of these impulses.

45
00:08:21,646 --> 00:08:25,560
Neither do we intend them
to carry out our contraction of muscles.

46
00:08:25,650 --> 00:08:28,141
Yet, as you can see, they work by themselves.

47
00:08:28,236 --> 00:08:32,565
But what if we block the nerve impulse
by simply applying local pressure,...

48
00:08:32,658 --> 00:08:35,694
..which can be done
with any ordinary metal clamp...

49
00:08:35,786 --> 00:08:40,282
..just at the swelling
on the posterior nerve roots...

50
00:08:41,625 --> 00:08:44,495
..for, oh, say... five or six seconds?

51
00:08:50,176 --> 00:08:52,501
Why, you mother-grabbing bastard!

52
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:56,716
As you can see,
all communication is shut off.

53
00:09:00,062 --> 00:09:03,016
ln spite of our mechanical magnificence,...

54
00:09:03,690 --> 00:09:08,731
..if it were not for this continuous stream
of motor impulses,...

55
00:09:08,821 --> 00:09:10,897
..we would collapse...

56
00:09:10,990 --> 00:09:14,323
..like a bunch of broccoli!

57
00:09:15,370 --> 00:09:16,365
Ohhh!

58
00:09:19,666 --> 00:09:22,073
ln conclusion, it should be noted...

59
00:09:22,669 --> 00:09:25,623
- Give him an extra dollar.
